1 A concurrent resolution urging Congress to provide veterans with medical coverage for
2 hyperbaric oxygenation therapy.
3 WHEREAS, the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention estimates between 1.6 million
4 to 3.8 million concussions occur each year; and
5 WHEREAS, efforts must be made to reduce the risk and health care costs for the country,
6 veterans, and others with brain injuries; and
7 WHEREAS, veterans injured in the line of duty deserve the best treatment our nation can
8 offer; and
9 WHEREAS, veterans suffering with traumatic brain injuries or posttraumatic stress disorder
10 are prescribed symptom-reducing drugs; and
11 WHEREAS, in essence, veterans are warehoused and discharged, dependent on costly
12 antidepressants and other antipsychotic medicines that promote dangerous dependencies and
13 may result in lethal interactions; and
14 WHEREAS, traumatic brain injury is one of the leading causes of morbidity and mortality in
15 the United States, accounting for approximately 2 million emergency room visits, between
16 230,000 and 500,000 hospital admissions, and 52,000 deaths annually in the United States;
17 and
18 WHEREAS, hyperbaric oxygen therapy is a medical treatment that enhances the body's
19 natural healing process by inhalation of one hundred percent oxygen in a total body chamber,
20 where atmospheric pressure is increased and controlled, and which is used for a wide variety of
21 treatments as a part of an overall medical care plan; and
22 WHEREAS, hyperbaric oxygen therapy and improving diagnostics have emerged as a
23 promising and effective treatment in healing injured brains and subsequently reducing, and in
24 some cases completely alleviating, the symptoms associated with the traumatic brain injury;
